---
title: Golden Tofu, Steak & Mushroom Marsala with Roasted Green Beans & Mashed Potatoes
description: This plant-based version of a classic Italian comfort meal is sure to satisfy! You’ll pan-fry tofu to golden-brown perfection, then coat in a velvety, savory mushroom sauce. It’s served atop creamy mashed potatoes with a side of tender, garlicky roasted green beans for a delicious, hearty dinner. Who says restaurant-style dining at home can’t be vegan?
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/657987c7bb715086aa4d051b-e2b3b2bc.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/657a1606ddd2bdfd232cc2b5.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 900 kcal
  fat: 48 g
  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 65 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 54 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 640 mg
course: main course
author: Sara Heilman
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/golden-tofu-steak-and-mushroom-marsala-657a1606ddd2bdfd232cc2b5
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: Southern Europe
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{16%ounce} into ½-inch pieces.

> TIP: For a smoother texture, peel potatoes first.

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches.
Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup potato
cooking liquid, then drain. Return potatoes to pot; keep covered off heat until
ready to use in Step 5.

While potatoes cook, trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Peel and mince or
grate @garlic{2%clove}. Trim and quarter @button mushrooms{4%ounce} (skip if
your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Roughly chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}.

Open and drain @tofu{1%unit}; press out excess water with #paper towels{}. Halve
crosswise, then stand tofu upright and halve vertically. Lay flat and cut into
½-inch cubes.

Toss green beans on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon},
half the garlic, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until tender and browned, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Pat chicken or steak dry with paper towels and season generously all over with
salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add @bavette steak{10%ounce}; cook steak until browned and cooked through, 5-7
minutes per side, or cook to desired doneness. Turn off heat; transfer to a
cutting board. Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, in a #shallow dish{}, combine half the @flour{2%tablespoon},
@salt{}, and @pepper{}. Add tofu; toss until evenly coated.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{3%teaspoon} in large pan over medium-high
heat. Add coated tofu and cook, turning occasionally, until golden on all
sides, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

> Use pan used for chicken or steak here.

Add @vegan mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} to pot with potatoes. Mash with a
#potato masher{} or #fork{} until smooth, adding splashes of reserved potato
cooking liquid as needed. (TIP: If potatoes have cooled, mash over medium-low
heat.) Season with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in pan used for tofu over medium heat.
Add mushrooms, remaining flour, salt, and pepper. Stir to coat. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until mushrooms are softened and lightly crusted, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir in @veggie stock concentrate{1%unit}, @mushroom stock concentrate{1%unit},
remaining garlic, and 2/3 cup water. Bring to a simmer; cook until slightly
thickened, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Add tofu to marsala sauce and stir gently until evenly coated.

Slice steak against the grain. Add steak to marsala sauce along with tofu.

Divide mashed potatoes and green beans between #shallow bowls{}. Top mashed
potatoes with tofu and marsala sauce. Garnish with parsley and serve.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.